110
00:05:49,920 --> 00:05:50,950
The starry sky here

111
00:05:51,510 --> 00:05:52,160
is really beautiful.

112
00:05:54,190 --> 00:05:55,510
Today is the Lantern Festival
in the mortal realm.

113
00:05:56,160 --> 00:05:58,390
Mortals make wishes upon shooting stars.

114
00:05:59,070 --> 00:06:00,070
Do you immortals

115
00:06:00,480 --> 00:06:01,510
make wishes too?

116
00:06:02,870 --> 00:06:03,630
You immortals

117
00:06:03,950 --> 00:06:05,360
probably don't have any wishes, do you?

118
00:06:07,240 --> 00:06:08,160
I didn't before.

119
00:06:08,600 --> 00:06:09,510
But I do now.

120
00:06:10,510 --> 00:06:11,480
My wish

121
00:06:11,720 --> 00:06:12,920
is for you

122
00:06:12,920 --> 00:06:14,600
to expel the fiendish aura within you

123
00:06:14,950 --> 00:06:16,000
and get back to normal.

124
00:06:16,390 --> 00:06:17,040
I guess

125
00:06:17,510 --> 00:06:19,270
your wish is the same, right?

126
00:06:25,950 --> 00:06:27,040
Yang, here.

127
00:06:27,480 --> 00:06:28,680
This is a birthday gift for you.

128
00:06:38,310 --> 00:06:39,120
Thank you, Master.

129
00:06:41,720 --> 00:06:42,560
In all my life,

130
00:06:43,360 --> 00:06:45,480
this is the first time anyone
has ever given me a birthday gift.

131
00:06:46,510 --> 00:06:49,310
No one's ever celebrated your birthday?

132
00:06:52,920 --> 00:06:54,070
When I was very young,

133
00:06:54,950 --> 00:06:56,480
a plague struck my village.

134
00:06:57,680 --> 00:06:58,480
My family

135
00:06:59,120 --> 00:07:00,000
was gone.

136
00:07:00,870 --> 00:07:02,480
After that,
I wandered from place to place.

137
00:07:03,430 --> 00:07:03,920
Then

138
00:07:04,120 --> 00:07:05,270
